RUGBY World Cup winning captain Siya Kolisi has reportedly been signed by Jay-Z’s Roc Nations Sports management. This is according to veteran sports broadcaster Robert Marawa who tweeted that that Kolisi was in London sealing the deal.  ??BREAKING??Isaac Lugudde-KatweDirector of Roc Nation International Sports Africa tells #MSW that Springbok Captain Siya Kolisi has joined @RocNationSports @RocNation family!!He's currently in London, signing them papers as we speak!!#MSW  US superstar rapper and businessman Shawn ‘Jay-Z’ Carter started Roc Nation and in 2013 branched out into sports management with Roc Nation Sports. The company describes itself as “elevating athletes’ careers on and off the field including endorsement deals, philanthropic endeavors media relations and brand strategy.”